parameters: \pop[4]Hey! Are you checking out Taylor's stream!?
\pop[4]Yeah! Him and Klace are live right now.
I've never seen his viewer count this high before.
\pop[4]People are going wild on social media, too.
I think he's about to set some records...!
\pop[3]A free celebrity endorsement? I'm not surprised.
Wish I could get something like that for my next novel.
\pop[4]Well it's not just for Taylor's benefit.
Looks like Klace is blowing up as well.
\pop[4]Well, there's not a lot of crossover between their two audiences.
Equal opportunity for \c[14]both\c[0] of them to make a big splash.
\pop[3]Do you think Klace expected that to happen?
\pop[3]He \c[14]did\c[0] say he'd talk to his publicist about it, right?

\pop[4]Shouldn't you be paying attention to the stream?
Don't normally have a camera on me like this.
\pop[3]Oh. You guys must be on some sort of delay.
Want to elaborate while you're here, at least?
\pop[4]Well, when I offered to stream with Taylor, I just thought it'd be fun.
But when I told the label, they really went wild with it.
Passion for me. Profit for them.
\pop[3]You could've just done it without telling them.
Isn't that why you wanted this hiatus to begin with?
\pop[4]I guess, but that would feel wrong.

It'd be hard to find a stadium you could fit that many people in.
This is like, one of your biggest concerts, and then some.
\pop[4]And nobody is expecting me to sing.
Gotta say, I kinda like the lack of expectation.
\pop[4]I was actually reading an article about that.
They say you're about to start a new trend.
\pop[3]Makes sense to me. You don't see many celebrities stream.
But here you are, even more famous than you were before.
\pop[4]Yeah, I'm refreshing my feed, and all I see is Klace and Taylor.
People are saying you bridged a gap, and made history.
Gotta say though, I'm feeling the need to brag.
\pop[4]I think I'll stay humble on this one.
\pop[2][Time passes, as we all watch the stream in our own rooms.]
\pop[3]You know, Klace is actually pretty good at video games.
\pop[4]Either that, or Taylor is letting him win.
\pop[3]I don't know if Taylor is capable of that.
These things are a matter of pride, remember?
Remember how bad he was at video games when \c[14]we\c[0] first met?
\pop[3]Also true. But are you okay with that...?
I mean, do you want your man with Taylor?
\pop[4]For the last time, we're not dating.
But even if we were, I wouldn't mind.
Taylor's a good guy, all things considered.
\pop[3]That's a \c[14]lot\c[0] of things to consider, Isaac...
Good to know you're open like that, though.
\pop[4]I guess Taylor's philosophy is rubbing off on me.
It makes me happy to see all of you having a blast together.
Before Klace arrived, I was worried our dynamic would suffer.
\pop[3]And here it is, doing better than ever. Setting records, too.
Gotta say, I'm glad you reminded me this was happening.
\pop[3]You know it. But I deserve a little break.
How long do you think they're gonna go for?
\pop[4]Looks like they've set a goal for an impromptu twelve hour stream.
And it looks like they might hit it. Wait, they definitely will. Oh, they just did.
\pop[3]Huh. And the little break becomes a big break~
Hold on. I'll cast the stream to the living room TV.
Wanna grab some junk food and meet me there?
\pop[2][I immediately put my phone down and sprint to the living room.]
